# Security Rules
- Use short-lived JWT access tokens and hash stored refresh tokens.
- Rate-limit auth and OTP endpoints; track OTP attempts and expiry.
- Validate uploads by MIME type, size, and content; store metadata safely.
- Use parameterized ORM queries, least-privilege access, and ownership checks to prevent injection and broken access control.
- Escape untrusted content and follow XSS-safe rendering practices.
- Store secrets in environment variables or secret managers, never in source control.
- Do not log tokens, passwords, card data, OTP codes, or other sensitive values.
